  "prompt": "Why is Quora blocking my name saying it doesn't conform?",
  "response": "Quora has specific guidelines for names on their platform. If your name is being blocked, it's likely violating one of these rules. Here's a breakdown of the common reasons why Quora might block your name:\n\n*   **It looks fake or generated:** Quora wants real people using the platform. Names that appear to be randomly generated or clearly made up are likely flagged.\n*   **It contains excessive punctuation, symbols, or special characters:** Quora typically wants clean, standard names. Avoid using a lot of numbers, emojis, unusual characters, or excessive punctuation in your name.\n*   **It includes titles, honorifics, or professional designations:** Avoid adding things like \"Dr.,\" \"Professor,\" \"CEO,\" or similar titles to your name.\n*   **It is intentionally misleading or impersonates someone else:** You can't use a name that suggests you are someone you're not, especially a famous or public figure.\n*   **It is offensive, hateful, or discriminatory:** Names containing slurs, hate speech, or content that is discriminatory against any group are prohibited.\n*   **It is overly promotional or contains a URL:** Quora doesn't allow users to use their name to advertise a business or website.\n*   **It's too long:** There is a length limit for names on Quora.\n*   **It's not a personal name:** Quora names are intended to represent individual people. Using a brand name, generic term, or other non-personal identifier may be blocked.\n\nHere's what you can do to resolve the issue:\n\n1.  **Review Quora's Name Policy:**  Make sure you understand the specific rules regarding names on Quora. You can find this in their Help Center or Terms of Service.\n2.  **Edit Your Name:** Change your name to something that complies with Quora's guidelines. Use your real, full name or a commonly used nickname that clearly identifies you.\n3.  **Contact Quora Support:** If you believe your name is legitimate and complies with the rules, contact Quora's support team. They 